<a name="Quiz Revolution">
<h4>
1.5.6. Quiz Revolution
</h4>
</a>
<p>
Quiz Revolution is a widely used test tool that is used by many T.V. stations and companies. 
One can create surveys and quizzes easily and save the questions online. One can also push their tests
and quizzes to facebook and there are many quizzes on the website that people can take. The testtool has
a very modern feel and look and it is simple to use and create tests and save questions. 
<p>
Overall, Quiz Revolution is a great easy to use testtool. It is a webbased tool so many different systems can use it.
<p>
<strong>Good Features:</strong>
<ul>
<li>
Widely used and because it's a webbased browser, it's widely supported.
<li>
Creating questions with video/pictures are easy. 
<li>
There are many options to randomize questions and change styles.
<li>
Publishing quizzes or surveys is easy.
<li>
The user can change the font and color of the text of the questions.
<li>
Allows the user to set a time limit per question.
<li>
Has a preview of the question as the user creates each question.
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bad Features:</strong>
<ul>
<li>
The free trial is limited to a couple questions.
<li>
The website has a popup saying that the question could not be saved most of the time.
<li>
Navigating throughout the website is hard because of the limited confusing tabs.
<li>
The overall layout of creating questions feels crammed and isn't convenient.
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Missing Features:</strong>
<ul>
<li>
Does not allow a preview of the entire test until the user creates everything. 
</ul>


